00:11:43.940 --> 00:11:45.240
there's this dividing line.

00:11:45.240 --> 00:11:47.600
And, you know, it's
not a bright line.

00:11:47.600 --> 00:11:48.900
&gt;&gt; Jonathan Haidt:
It's pretty bright.

00:11:48.900 --> 00:11:50.200
&gt;&gt; John Haskell: Okay,
then it is a bright line.

00:11:50.200 --> 00:11:51.500
&gt;&gt; Jonathan Haidt:
It's a bright line.

00:11:51.500 --> 00:11:52.800
It's amazingly bright.

00:11:52.800 --> 00:11:54.100
&gt;&gt; John Haskell: In 2014.

00:11:54.100 --> 00:11:55.400
&gt;&gt; Jonathan Haidt: Yeah.

00:11:55.400 --> 00:11:56.700
&gt;&gt; John Haskell: I'm going
to hit you with a series

00:11:56.700 --> 00:11:58.000
of questions about that.

00:11:58.000 --> 00:11:59.300
&gt;&gt; Jonathan Haidt: Okay.

