because we're all so subject

00:38:52.390 --> 00:38:54.790
to the confirmation
bias, we're all so --

00:38:54.790 --> 00:38:57.640
scientists are not just
really smart people,

00:38:57.640 --> 00:38:59.990
and they don't make discoveries
because they're so smart,

00:38:59.990 --> 00:39:03.210
scientists are productive
because they have an institution

00:39:03.210 --> 00:39:04.510
in which they're put together

00:39:04.510 --> 00:39:06.830
so that whatever they say
will be challenged by others.

00:39:06.830 --> 00:39:10.180
And it's that challenge process
that knocks down the bad ideas,

00:39:10.180 --> 00:39:12.970
that strips us of
our wishful thinking.

00:39:12.970 --> 00:39:14.270
Politics isn't like that.

00:39:14.270 --> 00:39:16.010
Politics, at its
best, can do that,

00:39:16.010 --> 00:39:17.710
that's what a deliberative
body is supposed to be,

00:39:17.710 --> 00:39:20.340
but they don't do that in
the Senate chambers anymore.

