So, yeah, so, the subtitle of
the book is, How Bad Ideas --

00:39:36.650 --> 00:39:39.480
How Good Intentions and
Bad Ideas Are Setting

00:39:39.480 --> 00:39:40.780
Up a Generation For Failure.

00:39:40.780 --> 00:39:43.260
Here are the three bad ideas
that the book is about.

00:39:43.260 --> 00:39:46.360
What doesn't kill
you makes you weaker.

00:39:46.360 --> 00:39:49.070
Always trust your feelings.

00:39:49.070 --> 00:39:53.740
Life is a battle between
good people and evil people.

00:39:53.740 --> 00:39:56.560
All three of these
are really bad ideas.

00:39:56.560 --> 00:40:00.040
All three of these are the exact
opposite of ancient wisdom.

00:40:00.040 --> 00:40:01.550
My first book, The
Happiness Hypothesis,

00:40:01.550 --> 00:40:04.340
had 10 chapters devoted
to 10 psychological ideas,

00:40:04.340 --> 00:40:06.020
that you find all
over the world.

00:40:06.020 --> 00:40:08.500
Those three that I just said
are the exact opposites of three

00:40:08.500 --> 00:40:10.690
of the chapters in
my first book.

00:40:10.690 --> 00:40:13.310
If we can teach our kids
to believe all three,

00:40:13.310 --> 00:40:16.010
